The basic required equipment as prescribed in the applicable airworthiness regulations (see Certification Basis) must be installed 
 in the aircraft for certification. This equipment must include a current Airplane Flight Manual, effective at S/N 681, S/N 
 15282032 and On, and S/N A1520809 and On. In addition, the following item of equipment is required: 
 1. 
 Stall warning indicator, audible, Cessna Dwg. 0511062 
 (Model 150 through 150E)

 (Model 150F through 150M (1977 Model)) 
 (Model A150K through A150M (1977 Model)) 
 (Model 152 and A152)

 loading instructions, when necessary, must be provided for each aircraft at the time of original certification.

 A1500609
